context:
KR:
&lt;거봐, 내가 할 수 있다고 했잖아…!&gt;
EN:
&lt;Hey, what'd I say? We got this...!&gt;

KR:
&lt;아, 아니야…&gt;
EN:
&lt;O-oh, nothing...&gt;

KR:
&lt;여, 역시 이상은 시간 현상에 있어서는 전문가라니까. 이왕 이렇게 된 거 이상이 좀 더 풀어서 설명해주는 게 어때?&gt;
EN:
&lt;W-wow, Yi Sang sure is a time expert, right? Can you summarize it in easier language now that we're talking about it anyway?&gt;

KR:
&lt;그런 걸로 직업이 생겨난다니, 좀 심한데…&gt;
EN:
&lt;It's really baffling to me that a job like that even exists...&gt;

KR:
&lt;그래도… 결국 이 열차가 도착하면 승객들이 전부 분류되어서 아무 일 없었던 것처럼 돌아갈 수 있겠네.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Still... I guess that means that, as long as the train arrives at the station, they'll all be put back together like nothing happened.&gt;

KR:
&lt;왜 그래?&gt;
EN:
&lt;Huh? What's up?&gt;

KR:
&lt;아, 비밀 이야기.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Oh. Time to whisper, right?&gt;

KR:
&lt;내가 대답해줄 수 있는 거라면…&gt;
EN:
&lt;Well, if there's anything I can tell you...&gt;

KR:
&lt;아… 안 그래도 묻고 싶었던 건데.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Oh... yeah. I actually wanted to ask you about that.&gt;

KR:
&lt;굳이 따지자면 뒤틀림에… 가까운 것 같긴 한데.&gt;
EN:
&lt;If I had to lean one way or the other, I'd say they're... closer to Distortions.&gt;

KR:
&lt;미안, 일단 둘 다 아닌 것 같아.&gt;
EN:
&lt;I'm sorry, I don't think they're either of those.&gt;

KR:
&lt;설명하긴 어렵지만… 뭔가 뒤틀림하고 굉장히 비슷한데… 달라.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Again, I'm not sure how I can explain this, but they're very, very similar to Distortions. But also... different.&gt;

KR:
&lt;이렇게 묻는다는 건… 파우스트는 모르는 거구나.&gt;
EN:
&lt;If you had to ask, then... I'm gonna guess Faust doesn't know?&gt;

KR:
&lt;…뭔가 미안하네.&gt;
EN:
&lt;... I feel like I should apologize for that.&gt;
